---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Acute Ischemic Stroke" description="Simulation case for acute ischemic stroke management.">
  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href={base}>Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href={`${base}cases/`}>Cases</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <span>Acute Ischemic Stroke</span>
  </div>

  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="card-tag">Neurological</span>
    <h1>Acute Ischemic Stroke</h1>
    <div class="case-meta">
      <span>⏱ Duration: 45 minutes</span>
      <span>📊 Difficulty: Intermediate</span>
      <span>👥 Team Size: 3–5</span>
      <span>🏥 Setting: Emergency Department</span>
    </div>
    <div class="tags" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <span class="tag">Emergency</span>
      <span class="tag">Neurology</span>
      <span class="tag">tPA</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Case Overview</h2>
    <p>
      A 65-year-old female, Mrs. Patricia Lane, is brought to the Emergency Department by her
      husband 45 minutes after he noticed she was having trouble speaking and her right arm was
      weak. She has a history of atrial fibrillation managed with warfarin.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learners must perform a focused neurological assessment, apply the Cincinnati/NIHSS stroke
      scale, determine tPA candidacy within the time window, and activate the stroke protocol
      while communicating effectively with the patient, family, and stroke team.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Patient Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Name:</strong> Patricia Lane</li>
      <li><strong>Age:</strong> 65 years</li>
      <li><strong>Gender:</strong> Female</li>
      <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 70 kg</li>
      <li><strong>PMH:</strong> Atrial fibrillation, Hypertension, Hyperlipidemia</li>
      <li><strong>Medications:</strong> Warfarin 5 mg daily, Metoprolol, Atorvastatin</li>
      <li><strong>Last INR:</strong> 2.8 (7 days ago)</li>
      <li><strong>Allergies:</strong> Aspirin (GI upset)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Initial Vital Signs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>BP:</strong> 178/96 mmHg</li>
      <li><strong>HR:</strong> 88 bpm (irregular — AF)</li>
      <li><strong>RR:</strong> 16 breaths/min</li>
      <li><strong>SpO₂:</strong> 97% on room air</li>
      <li><strong>Glucose:</strong> 6.2 mmol/L</li>
      <li><strong>NIHSS:</strong> 14 (aphasia, right hemiplegia, gaze deviation)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
    <ul class="objective-list">
      <li>Perform a rapid focused neurological examination using NIHSS</li>
      <li>Correctly identify a candidate for IV tPA based on inclusion/exclusion criteria</li>
      <li>Recognize the impact of anticoagulation (elevated INR) on tPA eligibility</li>
      <li>Activate stroke protocol and neurology consult within door-to-needle time goals</li>
      <li>Manage blood pressure appropriately in the context of acute ischemic stroke</li>
      <li>Communicate diagnosis and plan clearly to patient and family</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Scenario Progression</h2>
    <h4>Phase 1 – Recognition &amp; Stroke Alert (0–10 min)</h4>
    <p>
      Rapid assessment, stroke alert activated. NIHSS performed. INR result returns at 2.1
      (point-of-care test) — tPA exclusion criterion met due to anticoagulation.
    </p>
    <h4>Phase 2 – Mechanical Thrombectomy Pathway (10–30 min)</h4>
    <p>
      Team pivots to thrombectomy pathway. CT/CTA ordered. BP management initiated.
      Interventional radiology notified.
    </p>
    <h4>Phase 3 – Family Communication &amp; Transfer (30–45 min)</h4>
    <p>
      Neurointerventional team accepts patient. Goals of care discussion with husband.
      Transfer logistics arranged.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Debriefing Guide</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Was the NIHSS performed completely and accurately?</li>
      <li>How was the anticoagulation status identified and factored into the tPA decision?</li>
      <li>Was the stroke protocol followed with appropriate time benchmarks?</li>
      <li>How was blood pressure managed and monitored?</li>
      <li>How did the team communicate the shift from tPA to thrombectomy pathway?</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href={`${base}cases/`} class="btn btn-primary" style="background: var(--color-primary); color: #fff;">← Back to Cases</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
